OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1774966279
OL,3,CStarmer to meet with energy bosses as
OL,4,CIran war causes further spike in oil
OL,5,Cprice
OL,7,FAround the world, countries have begun
OL,8,Fto implement measures to combat the
OL,9,Frising cost of oil and fears of future
OL,10,Ffuel shortages.
OL,12,FIn Australia and the Philippines,
OL,13,Fgovernments have subsidised some forms
OL,14,Fof public transport in efforts to
OL,15,Fencourage the public to use their own
OL,16,Fcars less.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31817
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1774966279
OL,3,CStarmer to meet with energy bosses as
OL,4,CIran war causes further spike in oil
OL,5,Cprice
OL,7,FSlovenia, Myanmar, Sri Lanka,
OL,8,FBangladesh, South Sudan, and Ethiopia
OL,9,Fhave imposed some restrictions on fuel
OL,10,Fand electricity consumption, rationing
OL,11,Fthe amount consumers are able to buy.
OL,13,FSeveral other measures have been
OL,14,Fbrought in by countries like Egypt,
OL,15,Fthe Philippines, Thailand, Vietnam and
OL,16,FSri Lanka, including shorter opening
OL,17,Fhours, work from home mandates, public
OL,18,Fholidays, and alternating who is
OL,19,Fallowed to drive on any given day.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
